# `Navbar` component conventions

Patterns to preserve when editing `src/components/Navbar.tsx` (and when adding similar app-shell navigation).

## Client boundary

- **Directive**: `"use client"` on line 1 (string with double quotes, semicolon). Required because the component uses `usePathname()` from `next/navigation`.
- **Hooks**: Read the active route only via `const pathname = usePathname();` — no local state for selection.

## Data: route table

- **Location**: A module-level `const links = [...]` above the component (not inside the function), so the nav config stays declarative and easy to scan.
- **Shape**: Each entry is `{ href: string, label: string }`.
- **Paths**: App Router paths as strings; use **kebab-case** segments (e.g. `/cadastro-ativos`, `/listagem-aportes`).
- **Copy**: **pt-BR** UI labels (match project locale rules).

## Component API

- **Export**: `export default function Navbar()` — default export, no props. Keep the shell self-contained; do not add props unless the product explicitly needs configurable menus.

## Next.js `Link` usage

- **Import**: `Link` from `next/link` (App Router).
- **List rendering**: `links.map` with `key={link.href}` (stable, unique per route).
- **Attributes**: `href={link.href}`; avoid passing children as anything other than the label text unless design changes.

## Active route (selected tab)

- **Condition**: `pathname === link.href` (exact match; no `startsWith` unless you intentionally support nested active states).
- **Active classes**: `bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400` — aligns with project “accent / positive” (see `project-conventions.mdc`).
- **Inactive classes**: `text-gray-400` base; `hover:text-white hover:bg-gray-800` for hover. Include `transition-colors` on the base link class.

## Layout & Tailwind structure

- **`<nav>`**: `bg-gray-900 border-b border-gray-800` — app chrome (slightly above page `bg-gray-950` when used in layouts). **`sticky top-0 z-50`** so the bar stays above content while scrolling.
- **Width**: Inner wrapper `max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4` to match content width used elsewhere in the app.
- **Row**: `flex items-center gap-1 h-14 overflow-x-auto` — fixed bar height, horizontal scroll on small viewports, tight gap between items.
- **Per-link**: `whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium` — pill-like nav items, no wrapping.
- **Class merging**: One template literal for `className` with a ternary for active vs inactive branches (keep this pattern; avoid `clsx` unless the project already uses it in this file).

## Formatting

- **Indentation**: Tabs in this file (match existing `Navbar.tsx`).

## When extending

- New screens: add a `links` entry with `href` and pt-BR `label` first; only change sticky/max-width if the design system for the whole app changes.
- Nested routes: if you need “section” highlighting, document the new matching rule (e.g. `pathname.startsWith(...)`) in a short comment to avoid surprising UX.
